## Hints for Future Agents
- CRITICAL behavior nuance preserved: cerebras' async endpoint USES the async
  passthrough (async_passthrough=True); groq's async endpoint does NOT (groq's
  original groq_wrapper never wrapped async). Getting this wrong silently changes
  which op execution path runs. The Endpoint.async_passthrough flag encodes this
  per-endpoint difference — do not assume "async => passthrough".
- get_<provider>_patcher MUST keep its name+signature: patch.py resolves it via
  getattr(module, "get_<name>_patcher") and tests import it directly.
- LLMProviderPatcher caching mirrors the originals exactly: disabled -> fresh
  NoOpPatcher (NOT cached); enabled -> build once and reuse. reset() is new (the
  old module globals had no reset affordance; see audit F-D10).
- Migrating more providers: most are mechanical (endpoint list + keep the vendor
  accumulator/on_finish). The ones with bespoke should_use_accumulator variants
  (openai's Stainless raw-response guard, instructor's kwargs.stream) pass a
  custom should_accumulate per endpoint rather than relying on the default.

## Codebase Discoveries
- integration_utilities.should_use_accumulator is the canonical streaming
  predicate; the framework defaults Endpoint.should_accumulate to it when an
  accumulator is present, matching groq/anthropic/litellm/langchain_nvidia.
- OpSettings.model_dump() keys (name, call_display_name, postprocess_inputs,
  postprocess_output, kind, color) are all valid weave.op() kwargs — that's why
  weave.op(fn, **op_settings.model_dump()) works.

